Now I see the key issue! Look at `RegAPreCondOk` (line 1757-1758):

```c
LhsLo = &Lhs->A;
RhsLo = &Rhs->A;
```

But in `PreCondOk` (line 1598-1601):
```c
LhsLo = &Lhs->A;
LhsHi = &Lhs->X;
RhsLo = &Rhs->A;
RhsHi = &Rhs->X;
```

So `RegAPreCondOk` only checks `Lhs->A` and `Rhs->A` for LI_DIRECT, but NOT `Lhs->X` and `Rhs->X`. The `Opt_a_tossub` function then checks BOTH A and X. 

But wait, for `tossubax` with `OP_RHS_LOAD_DIRECT | OP_RHS_REMOVE_DIRECT`, the `RegAPreCondOk` only checks `RhsLo->Flags & LI_DIRECT` (i.e., `Rhs.A.Flags`) but NOT `Rhs.X.Flags`. But `Opt_a_tossub` needs BOTH A and X to have LI_DIRECT.

So the issue is in `RegAPreCondOk`: when `OP_RHS_LOAD_DIRECT` is set and `OP_LR_INTERCHANGE` is NOT set (like for `tossubax`), it only checks `RhsLo` (which is `Rhs.A`) for `LI_DIRECT` but not `Rhs.X`. But `Opt_a_tossub` needs both.

Let me verify this hypothesis by checking all the entries using `Opt_a_tossub`'s flags:

- `tossubax` with `Opt_a_tossub`: `OP_RHS_REMOVE_DIRECT | OP_RHS_LOAD_DIRECT`
- Looking at `RegAPreCondOk` for the `OP_RHS_LOAD` check (line 1774-1783):
  - It checks `RhsLo->Flags & LI_LOAD_INSN` and then `RhsLo->Flags & LI_DIRECT`
  - But RhsLo is always just `Rhs->A` when `OP_LR_INTERCHANGE` is not set

So for `tossubax`, `RegAPreCondOk` only checks if `Rhs.A` has `LI_DIRECT`, but `Opt_a_tossub` CHECK requires both `Rhs.A` and `Rhs.X` to have `LI_DIRECT`.

Now let me look at the same functions in `PreCondOk` (the non-RegA version) for comparison:

Looking at `PreCondOk` lines 1617-1626:
```c
if ((Desc->Flags & OP_RHS_LOAD) != 0) {
    if ((RhsLo->Flags & RhsHi->Flags & LI_LOAD_INSN) == 0) {
        break;
    } else if ((Desc->Flags & OP_RHS_LOAD_DIRECT) != 0) {
        if ((RhsLo->Flags & RhsHi->Flags & LI_DIRECT) == 0) {
            break;
        }
    }
}
```

In `PreCondOk`, both `RhsLo` and `RhsHi` are checked (A and X). But in `RegAPreCondOk`, only `RhsLo` (A) is checked.

