Let me check: `RemoveRegLoads` checks if `LI->A.Flags & LI_REMOVE` is set. My inserted entries don't have this flag. And they're simple `STA` and `LDA`, not tracked loads. So they shouldn't be affected by `RemoveRegLoads`.

Unless `DelEntry(D, D->PushIndex)` or `DelEntry(D, D->OpIndex)` shifts indices and my entries get lost...

`InsertEntry(D, X, D->PushIndex + 1)` inserts AFTER push. Then `InsertEntry(D, X, D->OpIndex)` inserts BEFORE op. Then `DelEntry(D, D->OpIndex)` removes the op entry. But wait, after the first insertion, the indices shift! So D->OpIndex might be wrong.

Actually, `InsertEntry` adjusts all indices automatically. So after inserting at PushIndex+1, OpIndex (which is > PushIndex) shifts by +1. Then inserting at OpIndex inserts before the op. Then `DelEntry(D, D->OpIndex)` removes the op (which is now at a different index).

But then `DelEntry(D, D->PushIndex)` removes the push. After the two insertions, PushIndex hasn't changed (insertion at PushIndex+1 doesn't affect PushIndex itself). So the push is correctly removed.

Hmm, but the inserted entries should remain. Unless they're being removed by some other mechanism.

